  <bioghist id="aspace_7bfce2af355f68fab23bf0ef275652f0">
    <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
<p>In the late 1950s and early 1960s, Cold War tensions and threat of nuclear war convinced government leaders in the United States that millions of lives could be saved by the construction of home fallout shelters. How-to booklets proliferated, instructing people in the fine points of building their own shelters, family preparations, first aid, and what to do in an emergency.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_2ddbdc48f29dab8c8ab1852b0ab2df13">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Collection contains 20+ pamphlets, booklets and newsletters on missle safety and how to prepare for and survive a nuclear attack (issued primarily by federal and state government agencies). Also, a circular nuclear bomb effects computer.</p>  </scopecontent>
